f, g
\max \{f + g \} \leq \max f + \max g
x
f(x)\le \max f(x)
g(x)\le\max g(x).
\sup_{x\in A} ( f(x)+g(x))\le \sup_{x\in A} \left( f(x)+\sup_{y\in A} g(y)\right)=\sup_{x\in A} f(x)+\sup_{y\in A} g(y)
\ max g(z):=g(z^*)
\ max f(z):=f(z^*)
f(z)\le f(z^*)
g(z)\le g(z^*) 
\forall z : (f+g)(z)=f(z)+g(z)\le f(z^*)+g(z^*)
\max(f+g)(z)\le f(z^*)+g(z^*)=\ max f(z)+\ max g(z)
